1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with connectivity-augmentation problems, which are a classic topic in algorithms and data structures. 
2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques, which are often studied in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper considers the cost of adding new edges to a graph, which is a common theme in game theory. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the fixed-parameter tractability of the connectivity-augmentation problems, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with connectivity in graphs, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture.
